{"title_page": "God's Gonna Cut You Down", "text_new": "\"'''God's Gonna Cut You Down'''\" (also known as \"'''God Almighty's Gonna Cut You Down'''\", \"'''God's Gonna Cut 'Em Down'''\", \"'''Run On'''\" and \"'''Sermon'''\") is a [[traditional folk music|traditional folk song]].<ref name=\"Loudwire\">{{cite web |url=https://loudwire.com/marilyn-manson-video-gods-gonna-cut-you-down/ |title=Marilyn Manson Releases Video for 'God's Gonna Cut You Down' |last=Hartmann |first=Graham |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref> It was first recorded by [[Golden Gate Quartet]] in 1946 and first issued later that year by [[The Jubalaires]].<ref name=\"second\"/> Since then, the track has been recorded in a variety of genres, including [[Country music|country]], [[American folk music|folk]], [[Gospel music|gospel]], [[alternative rock]], [[electronica]] and [[black metal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://avantgardemusic.bandcamp.com/track/gods-gonna-cut-you-down-johnny-cash-cover|title=God's Gonna Cut You Down (Johnny Cash cover), by Panzerfaust|publisher=[[Bandcamp]]|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref> The lyrics warn [[sin]]ners that they cannot avoid [[God]]'s judgment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/hear-marilyn-mansons-dark-rendition-of-traditional-american-folk-song-gods-gonna-cut-you-down/ |title=Hear Marilyn Manson's Dark Rendition Of Traditional American Folk Song 'God's Gonna Cut You Down' |publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAs \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\", it was performed by [[Odetta]] on ''[[Odetta Sings Ballads and Blues]]'' (1956), [[Johnny Cash]] on the posthumously released ''[[American V: A Hundred Highways]]'' (2006), and [[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]] as a non-album single in 2019.<ref name=\"Loudwire\"/> As \"Run On\", it has been recorded by [[Elvis Presley]] and [[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]]. The song has been covered by many other artists.<ref name=\"second\"/> A version by Bill Landford & the Landfordaires from 1949 was later sampled heavily for the 1999 song \"[[Run On (Moby song)|Run On]]\" by [[Moby]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whosampled.com/Bill-Landford/Run-on-for-a-Long-Time/ |title=Run on for a Long Time by Bill Landford and The Landfordaires |publisher=[[WhoSampled]] |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Johnny Cash cover ==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = God's Gonna Cut You Down\n| cover      = God'sGonnaCutYouDown.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Johnny Cash]]\n| album      = [[American V: A Hundred Highways]]\n| released   = July 4, 2006\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 2003\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Country music|Country]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whiskeyriff.com/2016/03/21/9-mlb-all-stars-their-country-music-walk-up-songs/|title=9 MLB All-Stars & Their Country Music Walk-Up Songs|date=21 March 2016|publisher=|accessdate=January 8, 2017}}</ref>|[[folk music|folk]]<ref name=\"Depression\">{{cite web |url=http://nodepression.com/article/johnny-cash-and-many-versions-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |title=Johnny Cash and the Many Versions of \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" |work=[[No Depression (magazine)|No Depression]] |date=July 22, 2013 |accessdate=February 24, 2018 |author=JeffK |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011141957/https://www.nodepression.com/article/johnny-cash-and-many-versions-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |archivedate=October 11, 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref>|[[gospel music|gospel]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/9934-ultimate-gospel/ |title=Johnny Cash: Ultimate Gospel Album Review |author=Klein, Joshua |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=February 28, 2007 |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>}}\n| length     = 2:38\n| label      = {{hlist|[[American Recordings (US)|American Recordings]]|[[Lost Highway Records]]}}\n| writer     = Traditional\n| producer   = [[Rick Rubin]]\n| prev_title = [[Hurt (Nine Inch Nails song)#Johnny Cash version|Hurt]]\n| prev_year  = 2003\n| next_title = Help Me\n| next_year  = 2007\n}}\n[[Johnny Cash]] recorded a version of \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" on ''[[American V: A Hundred Highways]]'' in 2003, with an arrangement quite different from most known gospel versions of the song.{{Citation needed|date=January 2015}} As of January 2016, this version of the song sold 672,000 copies in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://roughstock.com/news/2016/01/39651-the-top-30-digital-country-singles-january-25-2016 |title=The Top 30 Digital Country Singles: January 25, 2016|first=Matt|last=Bjorke|date=January 25, 2016|work=Roughstock|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA [[music video]], directed by [[Tony Kaye (director)|Tony Kaye]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.moviefone.com/2006/11/07/tony-kaye-no-longer-just-history/|title=Tony Kaye No Longer Just History|first=|last=by|date=November 7, 2006|publisher=|accessdate=January 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316084713/https://www.moviefone.com/2006/11/07/tony-kaye-no-longer-just-history/|archive-date=March 16, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> was made for this version in late 2006, three years after Cash's death. The video was shot entirely in [[black and white]] and features a number of celebrities: [[David Allan Coe]], [[Patricia Arquette]], [[Travis Barker]], [[Peter Blake (artist)|Peter Blake]], [[Bono]], [[Sheryl Crow]], [[Johnny Depp]], the [[Dixie Chicks]], [[Flea (musician)|Flea]], [[Billy Gibbons]], [[Whoopi Goldberg]], [[Woody Harrelson]], [[Dennis Hopper]], [[Terrence Howard]], [[Jay-Z]], [[Mick Jones (The Clash guitarist)|Mick Jones]], [[Kid Rock]], [[Anthony Kiedis]], [[Kris Kristofferson]], [[Amy Lee]], [[Tommy Lee]], [[Adam Levine]], [[Shelby Lynne]], [[Chris Martin]], [[Kate Moss]], [[Graham Nash]], [[Iggy Pop]], [[Lisa Marie Presley]], [[Q-Tip (musician)|Q-Tip]], [[Corinne Bailey Rae]], [[Keith Richards]], [[Chris Rock]], [[Rick Rubin]], [[Patti Smith]], [[Sharon Stone]], [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Kanye West]], [[Brian Wilson]] and [[Owen Wilson]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4530638/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast/ Johnny Cash: God's Gonna Cut You Down (Video 2006) - Full Cast & Crew - IMDb]</ref>\n\nThis version has appeared in the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] series ''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]'', during the episode titled \"[[What the Little Bird Told Him]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/01/gotham-recap-season-1-episode-12.html |title=Gotham Recap: Finally, a Decent Episode! |last1=Abrams |first1=Simon |work=[[Vulture (web site)|Vulture]] |publisher=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|accessdate=January 22, 2015|date=January 19, 2015}}</ref> It also featured in the season three episode of [[NBC]] series ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]'', \"[[List of The Blacklist episodes|The Director: Conclusion]]\", and in the [[CBC Television|CBC]] series ''[[Republic of Doyle]]'', where it closed episode 10 of season 2, \"The Special Detective\".{{CN|date=November 2019}}\n\nThe song is used by [[St. Louis Cardinals]] relief pitcher [[Andrew Miller (baseball)|Andrew Miller]], [[Los Angeles Angels]] relief pitcher [[Cody Allen]], as well as [[Kansas City Royals]] closer [[Brad Boxberger]] as entrance music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cleveland.indians.mlb.com/fan_forum/ballpark_music.jsp?c_id=cle|title=Cleveland Indians Ballpark Music|publisher=|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref> In Independent baseball, Tyler Nordgren of the Ottawa Champions also uses this song as his walk-up song.\n\nThe song is featured in the single-player campaign of ''[[Battlefield 3]]'', and a version of Cash's performance that was remixed by Ninja Tracks is used in the Gamescom gameplay trailer for ''[[Battlefield 1]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ymwXbF1VTKU|title=Battlefield 1 Official Gamescom Gameplay Trailer|publisher=|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe song is also used in the ''[[Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell: Conviction]]'' Launch trailer, and in the initial trailer for the 2010 [[Coen brothers]] remake of ''[[True Grit (2010 film)|True Grit]]''.\n\nThe \"Mondkopf Plus de Sommeil\" remix of Cash's performance appeared in an ad campaign for the all-new 2011 [[Jeep Grand Cherokee (WK2)]].\n\nThe song is also used in the [[Frostpunk]] Official Release Date Trailer - \"Serenity\".<ref>{{Citation|last=11 bit studios|title=FROSTPUNK {{!}} Official Release Date Trailer - \"Serenity\"|date=2018-03-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YPCgltNJoHI|accessdate=2018-03-31}}</ref>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2008)\n!scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKsinglesbyname|77|artist=Johnny Cash|accessdate=October 30, 2019|rowheader=true}}\n|}\n\n==Marilyn Manson cover==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = God's Gonna Cut You Down\n| cover      = Marilyn_Manson_-_God's_Gonna_Cut_You_Down_(Streaming_Cover).jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]]\n| album      = \n| released   = October 18, 2019<ref name=\"Amazon\">{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Gods-Gonna-Cut-You-Down/dp/B07YYWKKPH |title=God's Gonna Cut You Down by Marilyn Manson on Amazon Music |publisher=[[Amazon Music]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n* [[7-inch single|7\"]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = \n| length     = 2:40\n| label      = [[Loma Vista Recordings]]<ref name=\"Amazon\"/>\n| writer     = Traditional\n| producer   = [[Tyler Bates]]<ref name=\"Rolling\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-video-900640/|title=See Marilyn Manson's Creepy 'God's Gonna Cut You Down' Video |author=Grow, Kory|work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| prev_title = [[Cry Little Sister]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|Nu__TzWfpss|\"God's Gonna Cut You Down\"}}}}\n}}\n\n[[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]] recorded a cover version of the track during sessions for their tenth studio album, ''[[Heaven Upside Down]]'', which was released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/marilyn-manson-heaven-upside-down-exclusive-interview/ |title=Marilyn Manson: 'Heaven Upside Down' Needs to Be 'Chaos and Fuck Shit Up' |author=Hartmann, Graham |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=October 5, 2017 |accessdate=October 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018052545/http://loudwire.com/marilyn-manson-heaven-upside-down-exclusive-interview/ |archive-date=October 18, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> The song was performed live several times during that album's [[Heaven Upside Down Tour|supporting concert tour]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.spin.com/2019/10/marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-video/ |title=Marilyn Manson Buries Himself in New \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" Video: Watch |author=Burks, Tosten |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> Their studio version of the track first appeared on the [[Ethan Hawk]] film ''[[24 Hours to Live]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.loudersound.com/news/watch-marilyn-manson-face-the-grave-in-video-for-gods-gonna-cut-you-down|title=Watch Marilyn Manson face the grave in video for God's Gonna Cut You Down|author=Munro, Scott|work=[[Metal Hammer]]|date=October 18, 2019|accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> the soundtrack of which was issued via [[Var\u00e8se Sarabande]] on December 8, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/marilyn-manson-johnny-cash-cover-2151762|title=Marilyn Manson to cover Johnny Cash for film soundtrack|work=NME|date=October 19, 2017|accessdate=November 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111095240/http://www.nme.com/news/music/marilyn-manson-johnny-cash-cover-2151762|archive-date=November 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The song was then released as a standalone [[Music download|digital download]] and [[Streaming media|streaming]] [[Single (music)|single]] on October 18, 2019, in tandem with a tour by the band.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> A vinyl [[picture disc]] was released on December 13, 2019 and limited to 3,000 copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uklomavistarecordings.ochre.store/release/144851-marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |title=Marilyn Manson - God's Gonna Cut You Down, Vinyl LP, Loma Vista Recordings |publisher=[[Loma Vista Recordings]] |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> The vinyl single features one of Manson's [[watercolor]] paintings as its artwork.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/><ref name=\"Revolver\">{{cite web |url=https://www.revolvermag.com/music/hear-marilyn-mansons-snarling-rendition-folk-song-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |title=Hear Marilyn Manson's Snarling Rendition of Folk Song \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" |work=[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA music video directed by Tim Mattia, who previously directed the video for the ''[[Born Villain]]'' track \"Hey, Cruel World...\",<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> was filmed in [[Joshua Tree, California]] and was also released on October 18.<ref name=\"Revolver\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/10/marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-stream/ |title=Stream Marilyn Manson - \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" |author=Bacior, Robin |work=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/marilyn-manson-releases-new-single-video-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-2558487 |title=Marilyn Manson releases ominous video for new single 'God\u2019s Gonna Cut You Down' |author=Gwee, Karen |work=[[NME]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> The track peaked at number eight on [[Hot Rock Songs]] and at number one on [[Rock Digital Songs]]\u2014the band's highest peak on either chart.<ref name=\"HotRock\"/><ref name=\"Digital\"/>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n!scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n!scope=row| Canada [[Hot Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Marilyn-Manson/chart-history/CNS |title=Marilyn Manson - Chart History - Hot Canadian Digital Songs |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| 44\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|26|year=2019|week=43|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrocksongs|8|artist=Marilyn Manson|accessdate=October 30, 2019|rowheader=true|refname=\"HotRock\"}}\n|-\n!scope=row| US [[Rock Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"Digital\">{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Marilyn-Manson/chart-history/rock-digital-song-sales |title=Marilyn Manson - Chart History - Rock Digital Songs |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=July 10, 2019}}</ref>\n| 1\n|}\n\n==Other recordings==\n* The song was first recorded by [[Golden Gate Quartet]] on June 5, 1946 under the title \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\", and first released later that year by [[The Jubalaires]], under the title \"God Almighty's Gonna Cut You Down\".<ref name=\"second\">{{cite web|url=https://secondhandsongs.com/performance/159649/versions |title=Cover versions of God's Gonna Cut You Down by Golden Gate Quartet|publisher=secondhandsongs.com|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* Bill Landford and the Landfordairs recorded the track under the title \"Run On for a Long Time\" (2:34) on December 15, 1949, in Memphis, Tennessee.<ref>{{cite AV media notes |title=\"Run On For a Long Time\" [[b/w]] \"Troubled, Lord, I'm Troubled\" |type=liner notes |others=Bill Landford and the Landfordairs |publisher=[[Capitol Records]] |year=1949 |id=30203 |location=California, United States}}</ref>\n* American singer and civil rights activist [[Odetta]] recorded the song as \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" in the style of a 19th-century [[revival meeting]] preaching hymn, for her 1957 album ''[[Odetta Sings Ballads and Blues]]''.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/><ref>{{cite journal |journal=Liguorian |volume=63 |year=1975 |publisher=The Redemptorist Fathers |page=68 |title=Review |quote=In a marvelous new album of recorded folk songs (Vanguard Recording Co.), a gifted folk singer, Odetta, sings, 'God's A-gonna Cut You Down!' It is a powerful warning, in the style of the 'preaching hymn' of the old-time revivals and camp meetings which were such an important feature of frontier life during the entire 19th century.}}</ref>\n* [[Bobbie Gentry]] issued a version of the song, under the title \"Sermon\", on her 1968 album ''[[The Delta Sweete]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2013/jan/15/hidden-treasures-bobbie-gentry|title=Hidden treasures: Bobbie Gentry \u2013 The Delta Sweete {{!}} Music |work=[[The Guardian]]|last=Lynskey|first=Dorian|date=January 15, 2013|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* The vocals of the Bill Landford version were sampled by American [[electronica]] musician [[Moby]] for \"[[Run On (Moby song)|Run On]]\", a single from his fifth studio album ''[[Play (Moby album)|Play]]'' in 1999.<ref name=\"Depression\"/><ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/play-10-years-later-mobys-track-by-track-guide-to-1999s-global-smash-20090702 |title='Play' 10 Years Later: Moby's Track by Track Guide to 1999's Global Smash |journal=[[Rolling Stone]] |location=New York |date=July 2, 2009 |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |last=Weingarten |first=Christopher R. |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6GVTjSKeC?url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/play-10-years-later-mobys-track-by-track-guide-to-1999s-global-smash-20090702 |archivedate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* A version of \"Run On\" by [[Elvis Presley]] appeared on the 2004 [[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] compilation ''So High: Nashville Outtakes 1966\u20131968''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/So-High-Elvis-Presley/dp/B000189WYQ|title=Elvis Presley - So High|work=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]] recorded \"Run On\" for his 2010 album ''[[Praise & Blame]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://americansongwriter.com/2010/07/tom-jones-praise-and-blame/ |title=Tom Jones: Praise And Blame |author=Moore, Rick |work=[[American Songwriter]] |date=July 13, 2010 |accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* Kevin Lovatt's version of \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" was featured during the closing credits of the 2016 film ''[[The Hollow Point]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2918606/soundtrack |title=The Hollow Point (2016) - Soundtracks |work=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mercury Rev]] re-recorded [[Bobbie Gentry's The Delta Sweete Revisited|Gentry's ''The Delta Sweete'' album in 2019]]; their version of \"Sermon\" featured vocals by [[Margo Price]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/02/album-review-mercury-rev-shine-a-welcome-light-on-bobbie-gentrys-the-delta-sweete-revisited/|title=Mercury Rev Shine a Welcome Light on Bobbie Gentry's The Delta Sweete Revisited|website=[[Consequence of Sound]]|last=Ham|first=Robert|date=February 11, 2019|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\nJohnny Cash released a cover titled God's Gonna Cut You Down on his American V: A Hundred Highways album in 2003. A music video for the song was made in 2006.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eJlN9jdQFSc Johnny Cash - God's Gonna Cut You Down] on YouTube\n*[http://www.oldielyrics.com/lyrics/johnny_cash/gods_gonna_cut_you_down.html Lyrics \u2013 \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" (Johnny Cash cover)]\n\n{{Johnny Cash}}\n{{Marilyn Manson}}\n\n[[Category:Johnny Cash songs]]\n[[Category:Elvis Presley songs]]\n[[Category:Gospel songs]]\n[[Category:2006 singles]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Short Form Music Video]]\n[[Category:Year of song unknown]]\n[[Category:American folk songs]]\n[[Category:Anonymous musical compositions]]\n", "text_old": "\"'''God's Gonna Cut You Down'''\" (also known as \"'''God Almighty's Gonna Cut You Down'''\", \"'''God's Gonna Cut 'Em Down'''\", \"'''Run On'''\" and \"'''Sermon'''\") is a [[traditional folk music|traditional folk song]].<ref name=\"Loudwire\">{{cite web |url=https://loudwire.com/marilyn-manson-video-gods-gonna-cut-you-down/ |title=Marilyn Manson Releases Video for 'God's Gonna Cut You Down' |last=Hartmann |first=Graham |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref> It was first recorded by [[Golden Gate Quartet]] in 1946 and first issued later that year by [[The Jubalaires]].<ref name=\"second\"/> Since then, the track has been recorded in a variety of genres, including [[Country music|country]], [[American folk music|folk]], [[Gospel music|gospel]], [[alternative rock]], [[electronica]] and [[black metal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://avantgardemusic.bandcamp.com/track/gods-gonna-cut-you-down-johnny-cash-cover|title=God's Gonna Cut You Down (Johnny Cash cover), by Panzerfaust|publisher=[[Bandcamp]]|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref> The lyrics warn [[sin]]ners that they cannot avoid [[God]]'s judgment.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.blabbermouth.net/news/hear-marilyn-mansons-dark-rendition-of-traditional-american-folk-song-gods-gonna-cut-you-down/ |title=Hear Marilyn Manson's Dark Rendition Of Traditional American Folk Song 'God's Gonna Cut You Down' |publisher=[[Blabbermouth.net]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nAs \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\", it was performed by [[Odetta]] on ''[[Odetta Sings Ballads and Blues]]'' (1956), [[Johnny Cash]] on the posthumously released ''[[American V: A Hundred Highways]]'' (2006), and [[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]] as a non-album single in 2019.<ref name=\"Loudwire\"/> As \"Run On\", it has been recorded by [[Elvis Presley]] and [[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]]. The song has been covered by many other artists.<ref name=\"second\"/> A version by Bill Landford & the Landfordaires from 1949 was later sampled heavily for the 1999 song \"[[Run On (Moby song)|Run On]]\" by [[Moby]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whosampled.com/Bill-Landford/Run-on-for-a-Long-Time/ |title=Run on for a Long Time by Bill Landford and The Landfordaires |publisher=[[WhoSampled]] |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Johnny Cash cover ==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = God's Gonna Cut You Down\n| cover      = God'sGonnaCutYouDown.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Johnny Cash]]\n| album      = [[American V: A Hundred Highways]]\n| released   = July 4, 2006\n| format     =\n| recorded   = 2003\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Country music|Country]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whiskeyriff.com/2016/03/21/9-mlb-all-stars-their-country-music-walk-up-songs/|title=9 MLB All-Stars & Their Country Music Walk-Up Songs|date=21 March 2016|publisher=|accessdate=January 8, 2017}}</ref>|[[folk music|folk]]<ref name=\"Depression\">{{cite web |url=http://nodepression.com/article/johnny-cash-and-many-versions-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |title=Johnny Cash and the Many Versions of \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" |work=[[No Depression (magazine)|No Depression]] |date=July 22, 2013 |accessdate=February 24, 2018 |author=JeffK |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161011141957/https://www.nodepression.com/article/johnny-cash-and-many-versions-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |archivedate=October 11, 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref>|[[gospel music|gospel]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/9934-ultimate-gospel/ |title=Johnny Cash: Ultimate Gospel Album Review |author=Klein, Joshua |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=February 28, 2007 |accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>}}\n| length     = 2:38\n| label      = {{hlist|[[American Recordings (US)|American Recordings]]|[[Lost Highway Records]]}}\n| writer     = Traditional\n| producer   = [[Rick Rubin]]\n| prev_title = [[Hurt (Nine Inch Nails song)#Johnny Cash version|Hurt]]\n| prev_year  = 2003\n| next_title = Help Me\n| next_year  = 2007\n}}\n[[Johnny Cash]] recorded a version of \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" on ''[[American V: A Hundred Highways]]'' in 2003, with an arrangement quite different from most known gospel versions of the song.{{Citation needed|date=January 2015}} As of January 2016, this version of the song sold 672,000 copies in the United States.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://roughstock.com/news/2016/01/39651-the-top-30-digital-country-singles-january-25-2016 |title=The Top 30 Digital Country Singles: January 25, 2016|first=Matt|last=Bjorke|date=January 25, 2016|work=Roughstock|accessdate=November 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA [[music video]], directed by [[Tony Kaye (director)|Tony Kaye]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.moviefone.com/2006/11/07/tony-kaye-no-longer-just-history/|title=Tony Kaye No Longer Just History|first=|last=by|date=November 7, 2006|publisher=|accessdate=January 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180316084713/https://www.moviefone.com/2006/11/07/tony-kaye-no-longer-just-history/|archive-date=March 16, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> was made for this version in late 2006, three years after Cash's death. The video was shot entirely in [[black and white]] and features a number of celebrities: [[David Allan Coe]], [[Patricia Arquette]], [[Travis Barker]], [[Peter Blake (artist)|Peter Blake]], [[Bono]], [[Sheryl Crow]], [[Johnny Depp]], the [[Dixie Chicks]], [[Flea (musician)|Flea]], [[Billy Gibbons]], [[Whoopi Goldberg]], [[Woody Harrelson]], [[Dennis Hopper]], [[Terrence Howard]], [[Jay-Z]], [[Mick Jones (The Clash guitarist)|Mick Jones]], [[Kid Rock]], [[Anthony Kiedis]], [[Kris Kristofferson]], [[Amy Lee]], [[Tommy Lee]], [[Adam Levine]], [[Shelby Lynne]], [[Chris Martin]], [[Kate Moss]], [[Graham Nash]], [[Iggy Pop]], [[Lisa Marie Presley]], [[Q-Tip (musician)|Q-Tip]], [[Corinne Bailey Rae]], [[Keith Richards]], [[Chris Rock]], [[Rick Rubin]], [[Patti Smith]], [[Sharon Stone]], [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Kanye West]], [[Brian Wilson]] and [[Owen Wilson]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4530638/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast/ Johnny Cash: God's Gonna Cut You Down (Video 2006) - Full Cast & Crew - IMDb]</ref>\n\nThis version has appeared in the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] series ''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]'', during the episode titled \"[[What the Little Bird Told Him]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vulture.com/2015/01/gotham-recap-season-1-episode-12.html |title=Gotham Recap: Finally, a Decent Episode! |last1=Abrams |first1=Simon |work=[[Vulture (web site)|Vulture]] |publisher=[[New York (magazine)|New York]]|accessdate=January 22, 2015|date=January 19, 2015}}</ref> It also featured in the season three episode of [[NBC]] series ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]'', \"[[List of The Blacklist episodes|The Director: Conclusion]]\", and in the [[CBC Television|CBC]] series ''[[Republic of Doyle]]'', where it closed episode 10 of season 2, \"The Special Detective\".{{CN|date=November 2019}}\n\nThe song is used by [[St. Louis Cardinals]] relief pitcher [[Andrew Miller (baseball)|Andrew Miller]], [[Los Angeles Angels]] relief pitcher [[Cody Allen]], as well as [[Kansas City Royals]] closer [[Brad Boxberger]] as entrance music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cleveland.indians.mlb.com/fan_forum/ballpark_music.jsp?c_id=cle|title=Cleveland Indians Ballpark Music|publisher=|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref> In Independent baseball, Tyler Nordgren of the Ottawa Champions also uses this song as his walk-up song.\n\nThe song is featured in the single-player campaign of ''[[Battlefield 3]]'', and a version of Cash's performance that was remixed by Ninja Tracks is used in the Gamescom gameplay trailer for ''[[Battlefield 1]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ymwXbF1VTKU|title=Battlefield 1 Official Gamescom Gameplay Trailer|publisher=|accessdate=8 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe song is also used in the ''[[Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell: Conviction]]'' Launch trailer, and in the initial trailer for the 2010 [[Coen brothers]] remake of ''[[True Grit (2010 film)|True Grit]]''.\n\nThe \"Mondkopf Plus de Sommeil\" remix of Cash's performance appeared in an ad campaign for the all-new 2011 [[Jeep Grand Cherokee (WK2)]].\n\nThe song is also used in the [[Frostpunk]] Official Release Date Trailer - \"Serenity\".<ref>{{Citation|last=11 bit studios|title=FROSTPUNK {{!}} Official Release Date Trailer - \"Serenity\"|date=2018-03-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YPCgltNJoHI|accessdate=2018-03-31}}</ref>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2008)\n!scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|UKsinglesbyname|77|artist=Johnny Cash|accessdate=October 30, 2019|rowheader=true}}\n|}\n\n==Marilyn Manson cover==\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = God's Gonna Cut You Down\n| cover      = Marilyn_Manson_-_God's_Gonna_Cut_You_Down_(Streaming_Cover).jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]]\n| album      = \n| released   = October 18, 2019<ref name=\"Amazon\">{{cite web |url=https://www.amazon.co.uk/Gods-Gonna-Cut-You-Down/dp/B07YYWKKPH |title=God's Gonna Cut You Down by Marilyn Manson on Amazon Music |publisher=[[Amazon Music]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n| format     =\n* [[Music download|Download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n* [[7-inch single|7\"]]\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = \n| length     = 2:40\n| label      = [[Loma Vista Recordings]]<ref name=\"Amazon\"/>\n| writer     = Traditional\n| producer   = [[Tyler Bates]]<ref name=\"Rolling\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-video-900640/|title=See Marilyn Manson's Creepy 'God's Gonna Cut You Down' Video |author=Grow, Kory|work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| prev_title = [[Cry Little Sister]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|Nu__TzWfpss|\"God's Gonna Cut You Down\"}}}}\n}}\n\n[[Marilyn Manson (band)|Marilyn Manson]] recorded a cover version of the track during sessions for their tenth studio album, ''[[Heaven Upside Down]]'', which was released in 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://loudwire.com/marilyn-manson-heaven-upside-down-exclusive-interview/ |title=Marilyn Manson: 'Heaven Upside Down' Needs to Be 'Chaos and Fuck Shit Up' |author=Hartmann, Graham |work=[[Loudwire]] |date=October 5, 2017 |accessdate=October 28, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171018052545/http://loudwire.com/marilyn-manson-heaven-upside-down-exclusive-interview/ |archive-date=October 18, 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> The song was performed live several times during that album's [[Heaven Upside Down Tour|supporting concert tour]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.spin.com/2019/10/marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-video/ |title=Marilyn Manson Buries Himself in New \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" Video: Watch |author=Burks, Tosten |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> Their studio version of the track first appeared on the [[Ethan Hawk]] film ''[[24 Hours to Live]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.loudersound.com/news/watch-marilyn-manson-face-the-grave-in-video-for-gods-gonna-cut-you-down|title=Watch Marilyn Manson face the grave in video for God's Gonna Cut You Down|author=Munro, Scott|work=[[Metal Hammer]]|date=October 18, 2019|accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> the soundtrack of which was issued via [[Var\u00e8se Sarabande]] on December 8, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/music/marilyn-manson-johnny-cash-cover-2151762|title=Marilyn Manson to cover Johnny Cash for film soundtrack|work=NME|date=October 19, 2017|accessdate=November 11, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111095240/http://www.nme.com/news/music/marilyn-manson-johnny-cash-cover-2151762|archive-date=November 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> The song was then released as a standalone [[Music download|digital download]] and [[Streaming media|streaming]] [[Single (music)|single]] on October 18, 2019, in tandem with a tour by the band.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> A vinyl [[picture disc]] was released on December 13, 2019 and limited to 3,000 copies worldwide.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uklomavistarecordings.ochre.store/release/144851-marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |title=Marilyn Manson - God's Gonna Cut You Down, Vinyl LP, Loma Vista Recordings |publisher=[[Loma Vista Recordings]] |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> The vinyl single features one of Manson's [[watercolor]] paintings as its artwork.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/><ref name=\"Revolver\">{{cite web |url=https://www.revolvermag.com/music/hear-marilyn-mansons-snarling-rendition-folk-song-gods-gonna-cut-you-down |title=Hear Marilyn Manson's Snarling Rendition of Folk Song \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" |work=[[Revolver (magazine)|Revolver]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA music video directed by Tim Mattia, who previously directed the video for the ''[[Born Villain]]'' track \"Hey, Cruel World...\",<ref name=\"Rolling\"/> was filmed in [[Joshua Tree, California]] and was also released on October 18.<ref name=\"Revolver\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/10/marilyn-manson-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-stream/ |title=Stream Marilyn Manson - \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" |author=Bacior, Robin |work=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/marilyn-manson-releases-new-single-video-gods-gonna-cut-you-down-2558487 |title=Marilyn Manson releases ominous video for new single 'God\u2019s Gonna Cut You Down' |author=Gwee, Karen |work=[[NME]] |date=October 18, 2019 |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> The track peaked at number eight on [[Hot Rock Songs]] and at number one on [[Rock Digital Songs]]\u2014the band's highest peak on either chart.<ref name=\"HotRock\"/><ref name=\"Digital\"/>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n!scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n!scope=row| Canada [[Hot Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Marilyn-Manson/chart-history/CNS |title=Marilyn Manson - Chart History - Hot Canadian Digital Songs |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| 44\n|-\n{{single chart|Hungarysingle|26|year=2019|week=43|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrocksongs|8|artist=Marilyn Manson|accessdate=October 30, 2019|rowheader=true|refname=\"HotRock\"}}\n|-\n!scope=row| US [[Rock Digital Songs]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref name=\"Digital\">{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Marilyn-Manson/chart-history/rock-digital-song-sales |title=Marilyn Manson - Chart History - Rock Digital Songs |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=July 10, 2019}}</ref>\n| 1\n|}\n\n==Other recordings==\n* The song was first recorded by [[Golden Gate Quartet]] on June 5, 1946 under the title \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\", and first released later that year by [[The Jubalaires]], under the title \"God Almighty's Gonna Cut You Down\".<ref name=\"second\">{{cite web|url=https://secondhandsongs.com/performance/159649/versions |title=Cover versions of God's Gonna Cut You Down by Golden Gate Quartet|publisher=secondhandsongs.com|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* Bill Landford and the Landfordairs recorded the track under the title \"Run On for a Long Time\" (2:34) on December 15, 1949, in Memphis, Tennessee.<ref>{{cite AV media notes |title=\"Run On For a Long Time\" [[b/w]] \"Troubled, Lord, I'm Troubled\" |type=liner notes |others=Bill Landford and the Landfordairs |publisher=[[Capitol Records]] |year=1949 |id=30203 |location=California, United States}}</ref>\n* American singer and civil rights activist [[Odetta]] recorded the song as \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" in the style of a 19th-century [[revival meeting]] preaching hymn, for her 1957 album ''[[Odetta Sings Ballads and Blues]]''.<ref name=\"Rolling\"/><ref>{{cite journal |journal=Liguorian |volume=63 |year=1975 |publisher=The Redemptorist Fathers |page=68 |title=Review |quote=In a marvelous new album of recorded folk songs (Vanguard Recording Co.), a gifted folk singer, Odetta, sings, 'God's A-gonna Cut You Down!' It is a powerful warning, in the style of the 'preaching hymn' of the old-time revivals and camp meetings which were such an important feature of frontier life during the entire 19th century.}}</ref>\n* [[Bobbie Gentry]] issued a version of the song, under the title \"Sermon\", on her 1968 album ''[[The Delta Sweete]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2013/jan/15/hidden-treasures-bobbie-gentry|title=Hidden treasures: Bobbie Gentry \u2013 The Delta Sweete {{!}} Music |work=[[The Guardian]]|last=Lynskey|first=Dorian|date=January 15, 2013|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* The vocals of the Bill Landford version were sampled by American [[electronica]] musician [[Moby]] for \"[[Run On (Moby song)|Run On]]\", a single from his fifth studio album ''[[Play (Moby album)|Play]]'' in 1999.<ref name=\"Depression\"/><ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/play-10-years-later-mobys-track-by-track-guide-to-1999s-global-smash-20090702 |title='Play' 10 Years Later: Moby's Track by Track Guide to 1999's Global Smash |journal=[[Rolling Stone]] |location=New York |date=July 2, 2009 |accessdate=May 10, 2013 |last=Weingarten |first=Christopher R. |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6GVTjSKeC?url=http://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/play-10-years-later-mobys-track-by-track-guide-to-1999s-global-smash-20090702 |archivedate=May 10, 2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* A version of \"Run On\" by [[Elvis Presley]] appeared on the 2004 [[Bertelsmann Music Group|BMG]] compilation ''So High: Nashville Outtakes 1966\u20131968''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/So-High-Elvis-Presley/dp/B000189WYQ|title=Elvis Presley - So High|work=[[Amazon.com]]|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Tom Jones (singer)|Tom Jones]] recorded \"Run On\" for his 2010 album ''[[Praise & Blame]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://americansongwriter.com/2010/07/tom-jones-praise-and-blame/ |title=Tom Jones: Praise And Blame |author=Moore, Rick |work=[[American Songwriter]] |date=July 13, 2010 |accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n* Kevin Lovatt's version of \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" was featured during the closing credits of the 2016 film ''[[The Hollow Point]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2918606/soundtrack |title=The Hollow Point (2016) - Soundtracks |work=[[IMDb]] |accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Mercury Rev]] re-recorded [[Bobbie Gentry's The Delta Sweete Revisited|Gentry's ''The Delta Sweete'' album in 2019]]; their version of \"Sermon\" featured vocals by [[Margo Price]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2019/02/album-review-mercury-rev-shine-a-welcome-light-on-bobbie-gentrys-the-delta-sweete-revisited/|title=Mercury Rev Shine a Welcome Light on Bobbie Gentry's The Delta Sweete Revisited|website=[[Consequence of Sound]]|last=Ham|first=Robert|date=February 11, 2019|accessdate=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\nJohnny Cash released a cover titled God's Gonna Cut You Down on his American V: A Hundred Highways album in 2003. A music video for the song was made in 2006.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eJlN9jdQFSc Johnny Cash - God's Gonna Cut You Down] on Youtube\n*[http://www.oldielyrics.com/lyrics/johnny_cash/gods_gonna_cut_you_down.html Lyrics \u2013 \"God's Gonna Cut You Down\" (Johnny Cash cover)]\n\n{{Johnny Cash}}\n{{Marilyn Manson}}\n\n[[Category:Johnny Cash songs]]\n[[Category:Elvis Presley songs]]\n[[Category:Gospel songs]]\n[[Category:2006 singles]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Best Short Form Music Video]]\n[[Category:Year of song unknown]]\n[[Category:American folk songs]]\n[[Category:Anonymous musical compositions]]\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: Youtube \u2192 YouTube", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/God%27s_Gonna_Cut_You_Down"}
{"title_page": "M.O.D.O.K. (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = M.O.D.O.K.\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| genre              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Adult animation]]\n* [[Television comedy|Comedy]]\n* [[Science fiction]]\n* [[Superhero fiction|Superhero]]\n}}\n| based_on           = {{based on|[[M.O.D.O.K.]]|[[Stan Lee]]|[[Jack Kirby]]}}\n| creator            = {{Plainlist|\n* Jordan Blum\n* [[Patton Oswalt]]\n}}\n| starring           ={{Plainlist|\n*Patton Oswalt<ref name=\"Cast\">[https://deadline.com/2020/01/marvel-hulu-m-o-d-o-k-animated-series-veep-the-goldbergs-alums-patton-oswalt-cast-1202836764/ Marvel & Hulu \u2018M.O.D.O.K.\u2019 Animated Series Adds \u2018Veep\u2019 & \u2018The Goldbergs\u2019 Vets To Patton Oswalt-Led Cast Marvel & Hulu \u2018M.O.D.O.K.\u2019 Animated Series Adds \u2018Veep\u2019 & \u2018The Goldbergs\u2019 Vets To Patton Oswalt-Led Cast]</ref>\n*[[Aimee Garcia]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Ben Schwartz]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Melissa Fumero]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Wendi McLendon-Covey]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Beck Bennett]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Jon Daly]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n}}\n| composer           = \n| country            = United States\n| language           = English\n| num_seasons        = \n| num_episodes       = \n| list_episodes      = \n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Jordan Blum\n* Patton Oswalt\n* Karim Zreik\n* [[Jeph Loeb]]\n}}\n| producer           = \n| cinematography     = \n| editor             = \n| runtime            = \n| company            = [[Marvel Studios]]<ref name=\"MarvelTVFolding\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvel-tv-division-folded-studio-unit-layoffs-expected-1261586|title=Marvel TV Division Folded Into Studio Unit, Layoffs Expected|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 11, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211034642/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvel-tv-division-folded-studio-unit-layoffs-expected-1261586|archivedate=December 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br>[[Marvel Animation]]\n| network            = [[Hulu]]\n| first_aired        = \n| last_aired         = \n| website            =\n| website_title      = \n}}\n'''''Marvel's M.O.D.O.K.''''', or simply '''''M.O.D.O.K.''''', is an upcoming American [[Adult animation|adult animated]] [[Television comedy|comedy]] [[web television]] series created for [[Hulu]] by Jordan Blum and [[Patton Oswalt]], based on the [[MODOK|character of the same name]] created by [[Stan Lee]] and [[Jack Kirby]], that is set to premiere on [[Hulu]]. Originally intended as being part of a series of Marvel shows that would have lead up to a crossover titled ''The Offenders'', ''M.O.D.O.K.'' is now a stand alone series.\n\nThe series is produced by [[Marvel Studios]] via Marvel TV Studios with Blum serving as [[showrunner]].<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n\n==Premise==\nOusted as [[Advanced Idea Mechanics|A.I.M]]'s leader after selling it to GRUMBLE due to his constant failures at taking over the world, [[MODOK]] struggles with his marriage and family life as he faces a mid-life crisis.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Patton Oswalt]] as [[MODOK]], the \"protagonist\" of the series. The former leader of [[Advanced Idea Mechanics|AIM]] who is facing a mid-life crisis.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Aimee Garcia]] as Jodie, MODOK's wife who decides to pursue a new career change after running a mommy-blog.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Ben Schwartz]] as Lou, MODOK's socially inept 12-year-old son who does not have a care in the world.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Melissa Fumero]] as Melissa, MODOK's popular 17-year-old daughter who wants her father's approval.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Wendi McLendon-Covey]] as [[Monica Rappaccini]], MODOK's workplace arch-nemesis whom he is forced to work with.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Beck Bennett]] as Austin Van Der Sleet, MODOK's twenty-something new boss from GRUMBL, the company that buys AIM.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Jon Daly]] as [[Super-Adaptoid]], A robot who has high ambitions, but is stuck being MODOK's servant.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\t\n*[[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]] as Gary, MODOK's loyal henchman who is constantly optimistic.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n\n==Production==\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Hulu]] had given the production a series order, along with ones based on [[Hit-Monkey]], [[Tigra]] and [[Dazzler (Marvel Comics)|Dazzler]], and [[Howard the Duck]], leading up to a crossover special titled ''The Offenders''. The series was created by Jordan Blum and [[Patton Oswalt]] both of whom were expected to write for the series and executive produce alongside [[Jeph Loeb]]. Production companies involved with the series were slated to consist of [[Marvel Television]] and [[Marvel Animation]].<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web |last=Otterson |first=Joe |title=\u2018Howard the Duck\u2019 Among Four Marvel Animated Shows Ordered at Hulu |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/marvel-hulu-howard-the-duck-modok-hit-monkey-dazzler-tigra-1203134321/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |date=February 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Patten |first=Dominic |title=Marvel & Hulu Ink Pact For \u2018Howard The Duck\u2019 Animated Series + More \u2013 TCA |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/marvel-hulu-howard-the-duck-the-offenders-tigra-and-dazzler-hit-monkey-modok-1202554521/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |date=February 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |title=Marvel, Hulu Set Four-Show Animated Slate |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvel-hulu-set-four-show-animated-slate-howard-duck-modok-hit-money-tigra-dazzler-1185246 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |date=February 11, 2019}}</ref> Oswalt will also voice MODOK.<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldman |first=Eric |title=\u2018Marvel\u2019s M.O.D.O.K.\u2019 Creators on the Marvel Villain's Animated Series|url=https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/marvel-modok-creators-patton-oswalt-jordan-blum-talk-hulu-animated-series?linkId=63520830|website=[[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] |accessdate=February 12, 2019 |date=February 12, 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, it was reported that [[Marvel Studios]] will oversee subsequent development on the series after Marvel Television's closing and folding into the latter.<ref name=\"MarvelTVFolding\"/> In January 2020, Hulu's Senior Vice President of Originals, Craig Erwich, revealed that \"a few episodes of\" the series were already finished,<ref>{{cite web |author=John Schwarz |title=Report: Hulu Updates \"MODOK.\" |url=https://www.bubbleblabber.com/report-hulu-updates-modok/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |date=January 17, 2020}}</ref> followed shortly by the announcement of [[Aimee Garcia]], [[Ben Schwartz]], [[Melissa Fumero]], [[Wendi McLendon-Covey]], [[Beck Bennett]], [[Jon Daly]], and [[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]] as the series' cast.<ref name=\"Cast\"/> At the end of the month, Marvel decided not to move forward with ''Howard the Duck'', ''Tigra & Dazzler'', and ''The Offenders'', with ''MODOK'' and ''Hit Monkey'' continuing as planned.<ref name=\"MarvelAnimatedUpdated\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvels-howard-duck-tigra-dazzler-dead-at-hulu-1272751|title=Marvel's 'Howard the Duck,' 'Tigra & Dazzler' Dead at Hulu|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 24, 2020|accessdate=January 24, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125012137/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvels-howard-duck-tigra-dazzler-dead-at-hulu-1272751|archivedate=January 24, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hulu}}\n{{Marvel Animation}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:M.O.D.O.K. (TV series)}}\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Hulu original programming]]\n[[Category:Upcoming animated television series]]\n[[Category:Upcoming comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Animated television series based on Marvel Comics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name          = M.O.D.O.K.\n| image              = \n| caption            = \n| genre              = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Adult animation]]\n* [[Television comedy|Comedy]]\n* [[Science fiction|Science fiction]]\n* [[Superhero fiction|Superhero]]\n}}\n| based_on           = {{based on|[[M.O.D.O.K.]]|[[Stan Lee]]|[[Jack Kirby]]}}\n| creator            = {{Plainlist|\n* Jordan Blum\n* [[Patton Oswalt]]\n}}\n| starring           ={{Plainlist|\n*Patton Oswalt<ref name=\"Cast\">[https://deadline.com/2020/01/marvel-hulu-m-o-d-o-k-animated-series-veep-the-goldbergs-alums-patton-oswalt-cast-1202836764/ Marvel & Hulu \u2018M.O.D.O.K.\u2019 Animated Series Adds \u2018Veep\u2019 & \u2018The Goldbergs\u2019 Vets To Patton Oswalt-Led Cast Marvel & Hulu \u2018M.O.D.O.K.\u2019 Animated Series Adds \u2018Veep\u2019 & \u2018The Goldbergs\u2019 Vets To Patton Oswalt-Led Cast]</ref>\n*[[Aimee Garcia]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Ben Schwartz]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Melissa Fumero]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Wendi McLendon-Covey]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Beck Bennett]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Jon Daly]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]]<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n}}\n| composer           = \n| country            = United States\n| language           = English\n| num_seasons        = \n| num_episodes       = \n| list_episodes      = \n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* Jordan Blum\n* Patton Oswalt\n* Karim Zreik\n* [[Jeph Loeb]]\n}}\n| producer           = \n| cinematography     = \n| editor             = \n| runtime            = \n| company            = [[Marvel Studios]]<ref name=\"MarvelTVFolding\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvel-tv-division-folded-studio-unit-layoffs-expected-1261586|title=Marvel TV Division Folded Into Studio Unit, Layoffs Expected|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 11, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211034642/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvel-tv-division-folded-studio-unit-layoffs-expected-1261586|archivedate=December 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><br>[[Marvel Animation]]\n| network            = [[Hulu]]\n| first_aired        = \n| last_aired         = \n| website            =\n| website_title      = \n}}\n'''''Marvel's M.O.D.O.K.''''', or simply '''''M.O.D.O.K.''''', is an upcoming American [[Adult animation|adult animated]] [[Television comedy|comedy]] [[web television]] series created for [[Hulu]] by Jordan Blum and [[Patton Oswalt]], based on the [[MODOK|character of the same name]] created by [[Stan Lee]] and [[Jack Kirby]], that is set to premiere on [[Hulu]]. Originally intended as being part of a series of Marvel shows that would have lead up to a crossover titled ''The Offenders'', ''M.O.D.O.K.'' is now a stand alone series.\n\nThe series is produced by [[Marvel Studios]] via Marvel TV Studios with Blum serving as [[showrunner]].<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n\n==Premise==\nOusted as [[Advanced Idea Mechanics|A.I.M]]'s leader after selling it to GRUMBLE due to his constant failures at taking over the world, [[MODOK]] struggles with his marriage and family life as he faces a mid-life crisis.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Patton Oswalt]] as [[MODOK]], the \"protagonist\" of the series. The former leader of [[Advanced Idea Mechanics|AIM]] who is facing a mid-life crisis.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Aimee Garcia]] as Jodie, MODOK's wife who decides to pursue a new career change after running a mommy-blog.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Ben Schwartz]] as Lou, MODOK's socially inept 12-year-old son who does not have a care in the world.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Melissa Fumero]] as Melissa, MODOK's popular 17-year-old daughter who wants her father's approval.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Wendi McLendon-Covey]] as [[Monica Rappaccini]], MODOK's workplace arch-nemesis whom he is forced to work with.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Beck Bennett]] as Austin Van Der Sleet, MODOK's twenty-something new boss from GRUMBL, the company that buys AIM.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n*[[Jon Daly]] as [[Super-Adaptoid]], A robot who has high ambitions, but is stuck being MODOK's servant.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\t\n*[[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]] as Gary, MODOK's loyal henchman who is constantly optimistic.<ref name=\"Cast\"/>\n\n==Production==\nIn February 2019, it was announced that [[Hulu]] had given the production a series order, along with ones based on [[Hit-Monkey]], [[Tigra]] and [[Dazzler (Marvel Comics)|Dazzler]], and [[Howard the Duck]], leading up to a crossover special titled ''The Offenders''. The series was created by Jordan Blum and [[Patton Oswalt]] both of whom were expected to write for the series and executive produce alongside [[Jeph Loeb]]. Production companies involved with the series were slated to consist of [[Marvel Television]] and [[Marvel Animation]].<ref name=\"SeriesOrder\">{{cite web |last=Otterson |first=Joe |title=\u2018Howard the Duck\u2019 Among Four Marvel Animated Shows Ordered at Hulu |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/marvel-hulu-howard-the-duck-modok-hit-monkey-dazzler-tigra-1203134321/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |date=February 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Patten |first=Dominic |title=Marvel & Hulu Ink Pact For \u2018Howard The Duck\u2019 Animated Series + More \u2013 TCA |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/marvel-hulu-howard-the-duck-the-offenders-tigra-and-dazzler-hit-monkey-modok-1202554521/ |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |date=February 11, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |title=Marvel, Hulu Set Four-Show Animated Slate |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvel-hulu-set-four-show-animated-slate-howard-duck-modok-hit-money-tigra-dazzler-1185246 |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=February 11, 2019 |date=February 11, 2019}}</ref> Oswalt will also voice MODOK.<ref>{{cite web |last=Goldman |first=Eric |title=\u2018Marvel\u2019s M.O.D.O.K.\u2019 Creators on the Marvel Villain's Animated Series|url=https://www.marvel.com/articles/tv-shows/marvel-modok-creators-patton-oswalt-jordan-blum-talk-hulu-animated-series?linkId=63520830|website=[[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] |accessdate=February 12, 2019 |date=February 12, 2019}}</ref> In December 2019, it was reported that [[Marvel Studios]] will oversee subsquent development on the series after Marvel Television's closing and folding into the latter.<ref name=\"MarvelTVFolding\"/> In January 2020, Hulu's Senior Vice President of Originals, Craig Erwich, revealed that \"a few episodes of\" the series were already finished,<ref>{{cite web |author=John Schwarz |title=Report: Hulu Updates \u201cMODOK.\u201d |url=https://www.bubbleblabber.com/report-hulu-updates-modok/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |date=January 17, 2020}}</ref> followed shortly by the announcement of [[Aimee Garcia]], [[Ben Schwartz]], [[Melissa Fumero]], [[Wendi McLendon-Covey]], [[Beck Bennett]], [[Jon Daly]], and [[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]] as the series' cast.<ref name=\"Cast\"/> At the end of the month, Marvel decided not to move forward with ''Howard the Duck'', ''Tigra & Dazzler'', and ''The Offenders'', with ''MODOK'' and ''Hit Monkey'' continuing as planned.<ref name=\"MarvelAnimatedUpdated\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/marvels-howard-duck-tigra-dazzler-dead-at-hulu-1272751|title=Marvel's 'Howard the Duck,' 'Tigra & Dazzler' Dead at Hulu|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 24, 2020|accessdate=January 24, 2020|archiveurl